        "- This illustrates how **autograd** frees us from manual gradient derivation. We can then use these gradients in an optimizer to update `x` (or, typically, model parameters) during training.\n",
        "- PyTorch‚Äôs imperative style means we used standard Python control flow to compute `y` and `y_sum`. The framework built the computation graph dynamically and handled differentiation under the hood.\n",
